Class AdjacencyMatrixGraph<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.AdjacencyMatrixGraph<E>
  • public class AdjacencyMatrixGraph<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    Graph class. Elements (vertices) are immutable. Implemented using an adjacency matrix.

      • AdjacencyMatrixGraph

        public AdjacencyMatrixGraph​(E[] elts,
                            int sideLen)
        Construct graph with the elements in the input array. The vertices are connected as if they were in a square. Each vertex connects to the elements vertically, horizontally, and diagonally adjacent to itself inside the square.
        Parameters:
        elts - array of elements to be contained in the graph vertices
        sideLen - side length of the square the graph is simulating. Must be equal to the square root of elts.length
